<h1 class="govuk-heading-m">Role of data in DfE</h1>

<p class="govuk-body">
  In DfE, we collect and analyse plenty of data. Some of it is unique to each application, and some can be shared between applications.
</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">What is reference data?</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Reference data is a set of standard, agreed lists of values that many services need but no single service owns —
  for example countries, local authorities, schools or training providers. It changes rarely, so it can be defined
  once and reused everywhere.
</p>
<p class="govuk-body">
  In DfE, hardcoded reference data lives in the
  <a class="govuk-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://github.com/DFE-Digital/dfe-reference-data">dfe-reference-data gem</a>,
  which this site catalogues. Datasets that change more often ('almost' reference data, such as the schools list)
  are maintained by dedicated teams and are covered in the <%= link_to "guides", guides_path, class: "govuk-link" %>.
</p>


<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Role of SD Data Insights team</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
  SD Data Insights team can <b>provide support</b> when:
</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>you think a dataset is incorrect</li>
  <li>you need a new reference dataset</li>
  <li>you want guidance on using reference data</li>
  <li>you would like a dataset added to the platform</li>
</ul>
